Durban The 12-year-old South Coast boy who was shot dead after being mistaken for a monkey was in the tree chasing the pests away.Neighbours said they did not even flinch when they heard the shot on Sunday morning as the 87-year-old man arrested for the murder was the go-to &quot;pest remover&quot; for the rural community or Kwamahlathi in Braemer on the KZN South Coast. Neighbours said they were alerted by the cries of a friend Bongumusa Duma was playing with that Bongumusa had been shot dead. The incident happened on Sunday morning just before 9am. The man was arrested on the scene and a licenced shotgun recovered.He made a brief appearance at the Umzinto Magistrate s Court today but the case was postponed for Wednesday. The Mercury